// Unlike most WI_PATHS glyphs (which fill roughly their whole 30x30 box — e.g. the
// moon discs), wi-meteor's diagonal streak only occupies a ~15.5x22.1 sliver of that
// canvas (measured via getBBox: x 7.09-22.61, y 2.35-24.45), so rendering it with the
// same "0 0 30 30" viewBox as everything else leaves it looking much smaller/fainter
// than a same-sized moon icon next to it. This tighter viewBox (bbox + ~1 unit
// padding) fills the icon's allotted box instead, at the same size prop as any other
// WI_PATHS glyph.
export const WI_METEOR_VIEWBOX = '6.09 1.35 17.52 24.1'

// Same tight-viewBox treatment for the aurora curtain (bbox x 6–22.8, y 4.8–24.2
// + ~1 unit padding) so it renders at full weight beside the moon glyphs.
